The paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-agent imitation learning and validates it in a driving scenario. The algorithm involves reward augmentation and allows the designer to specify prior knowledge. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves a control scenario, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to analyze the driving scenario, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
